(Medicaid reimbursed) Medication sessions: $$150-500 per session (fee-for-service) Integration sessions: $$120-200 per session (Medicaid reimbursed) Resources and Verification Sources Primary Resources: FDA Spravato Information: FDA.gov Spravato approval documentation REMS Treatment Centers: Spravato HCP REMS Locator Clinical Trials: ClinicalTrials.gov ketamine studies Provider Directories: Psychology Today, state licensing boards Medicaid Information: State Medicaid websites, KFF.org Medicaid resources Verification Scripts: For Clinics: \"I'm a [State] Medicaid member seeking Spravato treatment for treatment-resistant depression. Do you accept [Plan Name] and what are your prior authorization requirements?\" For Therapists: \"I'm interested in ketamine-assisted psychotherapy. Do you accept Medicaid for therapy sessions and how do you coordinate with prescribing providers?\" Knowledge Base Document: Medicaid Ketamine Access Strategy Document Purpose: Comprehensive resource for navigating Medicaid coverage for ketamine-based mental health treatments Key Definitions: Spravato (Esketamine): FDA-approved nasal spray for treatment-resistant depression, administered in REMS-certified facilities REMS: Risk Evaluation and Mitigation Strategy - required safety protocol for Spravato administration Prior Authorization (PA): Insurance pre-approval process requiring documentation of medical necessity Treatment-Resistant Depression: Depression that hasn't responded to adequate trials of multiple antidepressants Coverage Criteria (Typical Requirements): Diagnosis of major depressive disorder or treatment-resistant depression Failed adequate trials of 2+ different antidepressant medications Documented psychotherapy attempts PHQ-9 scores indicating severe depression Psychiatrist referral and ongoing monitoring State-by-State Variations: Coverage policies vary significantly by state Medicaid program. Some states have expanded coverage while others maintain restrictive policies. Success Metrics to Track: Prior authorization approval rates Average time to treatment initiation Patient outcomes and satisfaction Provider network development Cost-effectiveness compared to traditional treatments Next Steps for Implementation: Choose your geographic focus area Research specific state Medicaid policies Identify and contact potential provider partners Develop patient education materials Create tracking systems for referrals and outcomes This represents a significant opportunity in the evolving mental health treatment landscape, with potential for both patient impact and business development as coverage expands and treatment protocols become more standardized. Copy Mixture-of-Agents Search Web"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=62347915-3ba1-4e00-8583-38d2c10e119e","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=62347915-3ba1-4e00-8583-38d2c10e119e"}]}]}]
